{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2>What is danger.js anyway?</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://danger.systems/js/\">DangerJS</a> runs during your CI process, and helps your team to automate certain manual code review tasks like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Is there a <code class=\"language-text\">new library</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">module installed</code>?</li>\n<li>Does this <code class=\"language-text\">PR changes</code> are added to <code class=\"language-text\">changelog file</code>?</li>\n<li>Is <code class=\"language-text\">.lockfile</code> kept up to date?</li>\n<li>Will this change <code class=\"language-text\">increase my bundle size</code>?</li>\n<li>So on and on..</li>\n</ul>\n<h5>Example: In <a href=\"https://github.com/facebook/react/pull/13695\" target=\"_blank\">React.js</a></h5>\n<center>\n  \n  <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695-d181b4ebafb44ae9f94b25e7b3aecf17-029df.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n  \n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 39.22222222222222%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"DangerJS in React\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695-d181b4ebafb44ae9f94b25e7b3aecf17-fb8a0.png\" srcset=\"/static/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695-d181b4ebafb44ae9f94b25e7b3aecf17-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695-d181b4ebafb44ae9f94b25e7b3aecf17-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695-d181b4ebafb44ae9f94b25e7b3aecf17-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695-d181b4ebafb44ae9f94b25e7b3aecf17-526de.png 885w,\n/static/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695-d181b4ebafb44ae9f94b25e7b3aecf17-fa2eb.png 1180w,\n/static/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695-d181b4ebafb44ae9f94b25e7b3aecf17-08f6a.png 1770w,\n/static/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695-d181b4ebafb44ae9f94b25e7b3aecf17-029df.png 1800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n  <i>React using danger.js ref:</i>\n</center>\n<h4>Integrating Danger.js</h4>\n<p><b>Step 1:</b> Add <code class=\"language-text\">dangerjs</code> to <code class=\"language-text\">your devDependencies</code> in package.json file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">yarn add danger -D</code></pre></div>\n<p><b>Step 2:</b> Create <code class=\"language-text\">dangerfile.js</code> file in your project.</p>\n<p><b>Example:</b></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token comment\">// Import the feedback functions</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> message<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> warn<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> fail<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> markdown <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"danger\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Add a message to the table</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">message</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"You have added 2 more modules to the app\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">//  Adds a warning to the table</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">warn</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"You have not included a CHANGELOG entry.\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Declares a blocking</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">fail</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`ESLint has failed with </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>fails<span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\"> fails.`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Show markdown under the table:</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">markdown</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"## New module Danger\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> dangerYarnInfo<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><b>Step 3:</b> Create an <code class=\"language-text\">github account</code> for <code class=\"language-text\">your bot</code>. (Optional)</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"October 16, 2018","path":"/blog/2018/add-dangerjs-to-your-project","title":"Add danger.js to your OSS in 5 mins"}}},"pageContext":{}}